The paper deals with music source separation using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to signal processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new DNN architecture, which involves training and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the theoretical relationship between STFT phase and amplitude, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
